<headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 12 at 10:52AM EST  by NWS Philadelphia - Mount Holly</headline>
<description>Moderate to heavy snow continues across the southern Poconos,
Lehigh Valley, far northwest New Jersey, and down into Berks
county. Northwest winds range from 15 to 20 mph with 30 mph
gusts. Visibility will lower to 1/2 mile or less in both falling
snow as well as blowing snow. There have been reports of as much
as 2 to 4 inches with locally higher amounts, especially in the
higher elevations, of snow across the area. Driving conditions are
treacherous. Please exercise caution if you must travel.
A Winter Storm Warning remains in effect until 7 PM EST this
evening.</description>
